Defendant Fantajah D Harris in court with Attorney Anthony J Procaccio.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State moves to have the court orally amend complaint to read location of the jail in the "City of Waukesha" rather than the City of Brookfield.   Court grants request.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Procaccio makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.   Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  FINE:  $473.50 &  $200.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid at $25.00 per month, commencing 11/1/16, alternate 13 days jail if not paid)   

 **Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.**   

***Expunction is conditionally granted after 6 months upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.***
